\f2\b \cf0 CrowdAlbum (2013\'962016)
\f0\b0  \'97 This was the closest match to your idea. It aggregated photos and videos from performances, helped fans live vicariously, and gave artists a visual history of their tours. Spotify acquired it in 2016, then quietly killed it. The gap it left has never been properly filled. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.androidpolice.com/2016/04/27/spotify-buys-photo-and-video-aggregator-crowdalbum/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Android PoliceAndroid Police}}\

\f2\b CrowdFlik
\f0\b0  \'97 Concertgoers checked in to an event, uploaded video clips, and the app organized shared videos based on location and time \'97 enabling users to create a composite video ("flik") from crowd-sourced footage. More of a video mashup tool than a media archive. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.bizbash.com/production-strategy/event-management/media-gallery/13481791/5-crowdsourcing-apps-for-events"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 BizBash}}\

\f2\b SureShot
\f0\b0  \'97 An AI platform that collects crowd-generated videos from concerts, festivals, and sports events. But it's 
\f2\b B2B
\f0\b0  \'97 event organizers pay to collect UGC for their own promotional use. Not a public fan-facing archive. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://sureshot.video/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 SureShot}}\

\f2\b Happaning
\f0\b0  \'97 Transforms fan videos into immersive experiences with AI-powered insight, focused on helping brands, festivals, and artists capture and own content their audience is already creating. Again \'97 B2B, not fan-community-forward. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.happaning.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Happaning}}\

\f2\b GuestCam / Fotify / Kululu
\f0\b0  \'97 Event photo sharing apps focused on weddings, corporate events, and private gatherings \'97 not public live events or sports. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://fotify.app/blog/best-event-photo-sharing-apps-2026/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Fotify}}\
