\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 Hero section\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 The header establishes credibility immediately. A few things worth calling out:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 The stats bar is load-bearing.
\f0\b0  "84 events archived, 12,480 photos" tells a new visitor this place is alive and worth their time before they scroll a single pixel. These numbers need to update in real time as uploads come in. For sports teams especially, archive depth is a flex \'97 "We have every Cubs home game since 2019" is a community achievement worth displaying.\

\f2\b Verification is a spectrum, not binary.
\f0\b0  You'll have three states:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Unverified \'97 community-created, anyone can suggest edits\
\ls12\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Claimed \'97 the artist/team/org has authenticated and can edit the bio and hero image, but fan uploads remain community-controlled\
\ls12\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Official partner \'97 paying partner, gets enhanced branding, analytics access, ability to feature picks\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The "claimed but not partner" tier is important \'97 give official parties control over their page's presentation for free. That goodwill leads to paid partnerships later.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Follow
\f0\b0  is a deceptively powerful feature. A fan following Cardi B gets notified when a new event page is created (upcoming show announced), when uploads start coming in after a show, and when their own uploads hit milestones. This is your retention and re-engagement loop. Follows also give you a dataset \'97 you know exactly which entities have the most passionate audiences, which is valuable for partnership conversations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 Events tab \'97 the core value\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 The events list is the heart of the page. A few design decisions here that matter:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Upcoming events show before past.
\f0\b0  When someone lands on this page before a show they're attending, you want them to immediately see the upcoming event, tap into it, and understand that this is where they should upload after. Pre-show anticipation is a powerful behavior trigger.\

\f2\b Thumbnail strips on past events.
\f0\b0  Four preview thumbnails on each event row are doing heavy lifting \'97 they communicate "this is a visual archive" without requiring a click. A row with zero uploads gets a muted "no uploads yet" state, which is an implicit prompt for people who were there.\

\f2\b Upload count as social proof.
\f0\b0  "345 uploads" next to an event row makes the next fan more likely to add theirs. Nobody wants to be the only person who uploaded from that show.\

\f2\b Filters you'll eventually want
\f0\b0  on this tab: by year, by tour, by city, by "has media" vs. all. Power users browsing a discography will want to jump to a specific era.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 Top Media tab\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 This is the discovery and delight tab \'97 the best stuff surfaced across all events, all time. Algorithmically ranked by likes + view time + recency weighting. This tab is what casual visitors browse. It's also what press or artists find when they Google the entity page and land here \'97 it's your showcase.\
An important decision: 
\f2\b what makes something a "top" upload?
\f0\b0  Pure like count is gameable and favors old content. A better signal is: likes per view within the first 48 hours of upload, combined with a time-decay factor. This rewards genuinely great shots from recent shows while letting all-time classics stay visible with a separate "all-time" toggle.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 Contributors tab\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 This is underestimated. The people uploading the most content to a Cardi B page are her most engaged fans \'97 exactly the people her management team would want to identify. This tab:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Rewards your best uploaders with public recognition\
\ls13\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Creates a status ladder (top contributor badges) that motivates more uploads\
\ls13\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Is a genuine product differentiator for partnership conversations \'97 "we can tell you who your top 50 superfans are in Miami"\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The contributor leaderboard should be per-entity and per-event. Being the top contributor at a specific show is a point of pride worth displaying.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 About / verification flow\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 The About tab does two things: shows data provenance (where event data comes from) and handles the claim/verification flow.\
