\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The core question first: what are you actually validating?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 There are two different bets embedded in this product and they require different MVPs:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Bet 1 \'97 Supply:
\f0\b0  Will fans actually upload their media to an event page? (Upload behavior)\

\f2\b Bet 2 \'97 Demand:
\f0\b0  Will non-attendees actually spend time watching fan footage to "virtually attend" an event? (Consumption behavior)\
Most products fail because they try to validate both simultaneously and end up with a half-built version of each. The smarter move is to sequence them \'97 validate supply first, because without uploads there's nothing to consume. But you want to do it in a way that also gives you early signal on demand.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
