\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The launch strategy \'97 don't launch to everyone\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The biggest mistake first-time founders make with a platform like this is posting on Product Hunt on day one and then watching the tumbleweed. You need content before you need visitors. Here's the sequence:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Step 1 \'97 Pick one artist, one show, one city (weeks 1-6, while building)
\f0\b0 \
Don't try to cover all entity types in the MVP. Pick music concerts first \'97 they have the highest upload motivation (fans 
\f7\i want
\f0\i0  to share their concert experience), the most passionate communities, and the most available setlist data. Pick one artist with a tour coming up in the next 4-6 weeks. Not a stadium act. A touring band or artist with 50k-500k followers, passionate fans, and a tour hitting multiple cities. Think: a popular indie artist, a mid-tier hip-hop act, a rising country artist \'97 someone whose fans are deeply engaged but who doesn't have a legal team watching for IP violations.\

\f2\b Step 2 \'97 Seed the first event before anyone else uploads
\f0\b0 \
Before you tell a single person about the platform, attend or recruit someone to attend the first show and upload 20-30 pieces of real content yourself. A mix of photos and short videos, from different seat locations. This seeding is essential \'97 an empty page gets zero organic uploads. A page with 25 existing uploads gets more uploads, because people can see it's real and active.\

\f2\b Step 3 \'97 Tell the artist's fan community, not the artist
\f0\b0 \
Don't pitch the artist yet. Find their fan subreddit, their fan Discord, their fan Twitter/X accounts. Post something like: 
\f7\i "I built a place to upload and watch fan footage from [Artist] shows \'97 here's the page for [Show] in [City], just happened last week. Who was there?"
\f0\i0  You want the community response before you're on the artist's radar.\

\f2\b Step 4 \'97 Measure before you build more
\f0\b0 \
After 2-3 events with real upload behavior, you'll know: how many people upload per show (your supply metric), how many people view without uploading (your demand metric), and which features people are asking for in comments/DMs. That data tells you what to build in Phase 2 \'97 not your assumptions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The metrics that actually matter at MVP stage\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Not DAU. Not revenue. These three:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Uploads per event
\f0\b0  \'97 your core supply health metric. Even 10-15 real uploads from a single show proves the behavior is real. 50+ from a single show is genuinely exciting. This tells you whether the upload motivation is there.\

\f2\b View-to-upload ratio
\f0\b0  \'97 for every person who uploads, how many people just watch? A healthy ratio is 10:1 or higher. If you're at 100 uploaders and 2,000 viewers on an event, you're building something. This validates the demand side.\

\f2\b Return visits
\f0\b0  \'97 does anyone come back to the same event page more than once? This is the strongest signal that the virtual attendance concept is working. Someone who watches clips from a show, goes away, and comes back the next day to watch more is exactly the behavior you're trying to create.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The one thing that will make or break the MVP\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Everything above is table stakes. The actual make-or-break factor is this: 
\f2\b the upload experience on a phone, 5 minutes after a show ends, has to be under 60 seconds from opening the site to finishing an upload.
\f0\b0 \
Think about the context. The show just ended. People are filing out. They're emotional, excited, maybe a little deaf from the speakers. They have 15 minutes before they're in an Uber or on the subway losing signal. If uploading to your platform takes longer than posting to Instagram Stories, they will post to Instagram Stories instead and you get nothing.\
That means:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls21\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The event page URL needs to be reachable from a QR code they scanned on the way in (or a link in bio they tapped before the show)\
\ls21\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 No forced account creation before uploading\
\ls21\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The file picker opens immediately \'97 no multi-screen onboarding flow\
