\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 The practical takeaway for your build\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 This validation map tells you something important about sequencing:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 You don't need to prove upload behavior from scratch
\f0\b0  \'97 the adjacent evidence is strong enough to proceed with reasonable confidence. Fans film everything. They share everything. They contribute to archives they care about. The specific question of "will they upload directly to your platform without organizer prompting" is the one gap, and the answer is almost certainly yes 
\f7\i if
\f0\i0  the friction is low enough and the page they're uploading to has existing content. Which is why the seeding strategy from the MVP plan matters so much.\

\f2\b The virtual attendance session length is the only thing you genuinely don't know.
\f0\b0  And here's the good news: you don't need to solve it in the MVP. You just need to measure it. Put Plausible or Fathom analytics on the event pages from day one, track average session duration and page depth, and within 3-4 events you'll have real data. If non-attendees are spending 8 minutes on an event page, you have a signal. If they're spending 45 minutes, you have a product.\

\f2\b The pricing-out trend is your structural tailwind.
\f0\b0  Concert ticket prices are up 50% since 2019 and every industry analyst expects them to keep rising. One in five Gen Z fans already spent beyond their means to attend shows. The Live Nation CEO has literally said tickets are still underpriced. This isn't a temporary condition \'97 it's the permanent reality of the live events industry. Every year that passes, your potential audience of priced-out fans gets larger. That's a tailwind most startups would pay for. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/23/concert-ticket-prices-live-music-demand.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 CNBC}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.billboard.com/pro/concert-ticket-prices-studies-spending-debt-consumer-trends/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Billboard}}\
The companies before you proved the content exists and the desire exists. You're the first to try to organize it into a real viewing experience for the people who weren't there. That's the unproven piece \'97 and it's also the most valuable one if it works.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

