\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 Concert Archives \'97 the closest existing thing\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 Concert Archives is a social network and diary for music fans to remember and share concerts they've attended. Under each specific show date and venue, fans can upload photos and videos, view media uploaded by other attendees, and check the setlist. It's been running since 2013, has been featured in The New York Times, Newsweek, The Guardian, Reuters, BuzzFeed, and Pitchfork. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://concert-archives.en.softonic.com/android"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Softonic}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=org.concertarchives&hl=en_US"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Google Play}}\
This is genuinely the closest thing to what you're building. It has the entity 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  event hierarchy, it has photo/video uploads, it has setlist integration. You need to take it seriously.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 But here's what the reviews tell you:
\f0\b0  Users consistently say "great idea, needs a LOT of work" \'97 the app overheats phones, archives don't load, there are duplicate shows, bugs crash sessions after hours of data entry. It's a passion project that never got proper product investment. Their Facebook page has 1,560 likes. After 12 years. That's not a thriving platform \'97 that's a concept that validated demand but never had the execution to capture it. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://justuseapp.com/en/app/1531993239/concert-archives/reviews"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 JustUseApp}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.facebook.com/concertarchives/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Facebook}}\

\f2\b The critical gap:
\f0\b0  Concert Archives is built for attendees logging their own history. It's a personal diary with sharing features. It is NOT built around the virtual attendance experience \'97 the non-attendee consuming the full show. That reframe is still unoccupied.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 FanVids \'97 very recent, very relevant\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 This is the most important new competitor. FanVids launched in March 2026 \'97 a free app that lets artists collect fan videos at live shows, share them with other fans, and collect fan data. Growing since its April 2024 launch, FanVids has worked with hundreds of artists including Kelsea Ballerini and Billy Idol. Monthly users increased tenfold in just three months. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://celebrityaccess.com/2026/03/04/free-app-fanvids-turns-live-fan-videos-into-a-marketing-asset"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 CelebrityAccess}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://limitless-magazine.com/2025/08/28/fanvids-reshaping-the-live-entertainment-experience/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Limitless-magazine}}\
This is real traction and recent. You need to look at this seriously.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 But the model is still B2B-artist-first:
\f0\b0  FanVids is built for artists, labels, and managers to collect fan UGC and first-party data for their CRM, ticket sales, and merch. The pitch is: "fans upload content directly to you, and you capture their contact info in the process." The fan experience is secondary \'97 it's a marketing data pipeline that also happens to show fans each other's videos. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.fanvids.io/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Fanvids}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://stack.rostr.cc/stacks/laylo-ceo-s-direct-to-fan-tech-stack-7-tools-for-artists-to-build-an-owned-audience-2026"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Rostr}}\
The artist owns the page. The artist controls it. A fan browsing FanVids is browsing the 
\f7\i artist's
\f0\i0  marketing tool. That's fundamentally different from a community-owned fan archive where no single party controls the content.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 Aftershow.io \'97 same B2B lane\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 Aftershow.io lets artists collect unlimited videos and photos from fans with smart upload management, branded URLs, separate landing pages for every concert, geographic visualization of upload activity, and dynamic QR codes for printing on merch and posters. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aftershow.io/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 aftershow}}\
Again \'97 artist-controlled, B2B model, fan data capture is the core value prop. Same lane as FanVids and SureShot.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
