\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The practical breakdown\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Opus excels at initial builds based on project plans, adding entire new modules, complex system design, and multi-system integration. That describes the first session with your scope document perfectly. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://stevekinney.com/courses/ai-development/claude-code-model-selection"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Steve Kinney}}\
Sonnet 4.6 handles 90%+ of coding tasks without compromise and is preferred over Opus 4.5 by 59% of developers for day-to-day work. Once the architecture is established and you're iterating on individual components, straight Sonnet is fine and meaningfully cheaper. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claudefa.st/blog/models"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Claude Fast}}\
Max and Team Premium plans default to Opus 4.6, while Pro and Team Standard default to Sonnet 4.6. Claude Code may automatically fall back to Sonnet if you hit a usage threshold with Opus. So check your plan \'97 if you're on Pro, you may not have Opus access at all, in which case Sonnet 4.6 is your answer and it'll handle this build just fine. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://dev.to/klement_gunndu/pick-the-right-claude-code-model-for-every-task-1p6a"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 DEV Community}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 Practical session strategy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Session 1 \'97 Architecture and database:
\f0\b0  Use Opus or opusplan. Feed it the full scope document. Let it set up the Next.js project, Supabase schema, and all the API routes before touching any UI. This is where the reasoning investment pays off.\

\f2\b Sessions 2\'964 \'97 Page by page:
\f0\b0  Sonnet is fine. The architecture is decided, you're just implementing. Start each session with a 
\f6\fs26 /clear
\f0\fs24  and tell it which page you're building.\

\f2\b Debugging sessions:
\f0\b0  Switch back to Opus with 
\f6\fs26 /model opus
\f0\fs24  when something is genuinely broken and you need it to reason across multiple files to find the issue.\
One other thing worth knowing: you can run 
\f6\fs26 /model
\f0\fs24  at any point during a session to switch instantly \'97 you don't have to restart. So start on Opus for the planning phase of a session and drop to Sonnet once you're in pure implementation mode. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/model-config"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 \strokec6 Claude}}\
