Showside \'97 Project Instructions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 What Showside is\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Showside is a fan media platform for live events. People who attend concerts, sports games, races, and other live events upload their photos and videos to dedicated event pages. Everyone else \'97 people who couldn't get tickets, couldn't afford them, live in another city or country, or simply want to relive the experience \'97 watches, browses, and virtually attends through the fan-captured footage.\
The platform sits at the intersection of two proven behaviors: fans already film everything at live events and post it to social media, and non-attendees already watch that content in huge numbers on YouTube and TikTok. What doesn't exist is an organized, permanent, structured destination for that content. Showside is that destination.\
The one-line pitch: 
\f2\b "The show, from everyone who was there."
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The problem it solves\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Concert ticket prices have risen 50% since 2019. The average top-100 tour ticket hit $136 in 2024. Taylor Swift resale tickets averaged over $1,000. One in five Gen Z fans spent beyond their means just to attend a show. For every person inside a venue, many more wanted to be there and couldn't.\
When those fans search YouTube for "Taylor Swift Philadelphia concert," they get a random pile of clips uploaded by different people, in no particular order, with no structure \'97 no way to find every clip from that specific night, no setlist context, no ability to browse by seat section or song. The content exists. The organization doesn't.\
Showside takes that same raw material \'97 fan-shot phone footage \'97 and turns it into a structured, navigable show experience for the people who weren't there.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The core mental model\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Experience-first, archive-second.
\f0\b0 \
The primary user is someone who didn't attend. She's a 16-year-old in London who loves Morgan Wallen and will never afford a stadium ticket. She lands on his Showside page and within 30 seconds she's watching fan-shot video from the floor pit of last week's Boston show. She doesn't need to pick a specific date or venue to get there. The best content surfaces automatically.\
The archive \'97 every specific show, every setlist, every upload organized by date and venue \'97 is real, valuable, and fully accessible. It's just not the front door. It lives behind a single click for the fans who want that level of detail: the superfan who knows exactly which night Morgan played a surprise cover, the attendee who wants to find their own uploads, the person who wants to compare night 1 vs night 2 of a two-night stand.\
This is the key product distinction that separates Showside from everything that has been tried before. Concert Archives (the closest existing competitor, launched 2013) is a diary \'97 built for attendees to log their own history. Showside is a broadcast \'97 built for everyone who wasn't there.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 How it works\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 The three-tier hierarchy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Tier 1 \'97 Entity pages
\f0\b0  (
\f6\fs26 /morgan-wallen
\f0\fs24 , 
\f6\fs26 /philadelphia-phillies
\f0\fs24 , 
\f6\fs26 /kentucky-derby
\f0\fs24 ) Permanent, evergreen pages for any recurring subject that generates live events. Types include: music artists, sports teams, recurring event brands (Kentucky Derby, Indy 500, Coachella), and venues. The entity page is the experience layer \'97 it surfaces the best fan content across all shows, all time, without requiring visitors to pick a specific date first.\

\f2\b Tier 2 \'97 Event pages
\f0\b0  (
\f6\fs26 /morgan-wallen/morgan-wallen-gillette-stadium-boston-2026-05-10
\f0\fs24 ) Each specific show, game, or event gets a permanent URL. Tied to a venue, date, city, and optionally a tour name and setlist. This is where uploads attach. The event page has three views: Watch (curated experience for non-attendees), Browse (full unfiltered grid), and Upload (the fan contribution flow).\

\f2\b Tier 3 \'97 Media
\f0\b0  Individual photos and videos uploaded by fans. Each piece of media can be tagged to a specific song from the event's setlist, a seat section (floor, section 100s, upper deck, stage left/right), and an optional caption. Media items have like counts, view counts, and uploader attribution (anonymous or named).\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The entity page in detail\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The entity page is the most important page on the platform. It must deliver the virtual attendance experience without requiring any navigation decisions from a casual visitor.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Hero section:
\f0\b0  Dark, cinematic background using a real fan photo or gradient. Right side shows a 2\'d73 grid of the top 6 most-viewed video thumbnails for this entity \'97 real content, immediately visible, before any scroll. Left side overlaid on the dark background: entity name, genre badge, verified badge if applicable, follow button, follower count. Below the hero: a stat strip showing total photos & videos / shows covered / contributors / earliest show year.\

\f2\b Fan highlights section:
\f0\b0  The core of the page. A filter pill row lets visitors sort by: All time best / Crowd energy / Stage moments / Acoustic / Most recent. Below the pills: one large hero card (spans two rows) plus four smaller cards in a 2\'d72 grid. Each card shows a video thumbnail, play button, duration, song tag or caption, like count, uploader handle, and venue/city. This section answers "what is a Morgan Wallen concert like?" without requiring any further navigation.\

\f2\b Most filmed songs section:
\f0\b0  A 5-column grid showing the songs that have the most fan clips across all shows \'97 song name, clip count, a relative bar showing volume. Clicking a song filters the page to show all clips of that song from any show. This is a crucial feature: a fan who wants to see every clip of "Last Night" from any show anywhere can get there in one tap, without knowing or caring which specific event it came from.\

\f2\b Recent shows section:
\f0\b0  Four event cards showing the most recent shows with upload counts and thumbnail previews. This is a "go deeper" prompt, not the primary content.\

\f2\b Full archive:
\f0\b0  Collapsed by default behind an "All N shows 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0 " link. When expanded, shows a chronological list of every event grouped by year. This is the archive \'97 real, permanent, fully accessible. It's just not where most visitors start.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The event page in detail\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The event page serves two audiences simultaneously: the attendee who was there and wants to find/upload content, and the non-attendee who wants to experience the show.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Watch tab (default):
\f0\b0  Opens with the most-viewed video for this event playing full-width via Mux player. Below the player: a horizontal scroll of other video clips. If setlist data exists, a "Browse by song" section lists all songs in performance order \'97 each shows a clip count and is tappable to filter the media grid below. This lets a non-attendee step through the show song by song like chapters in a documentary.\

\f2\b Browse tab:
\f0\b0  Full unfiltered media grid with filter controls: All / Photos / Videos, and section pills (Floor/Pit, Section 100s, Section 200s, Upper deck, Stage left, Stage right). This is for people who want to explore rather than be guided.\

\f2\b Upload tab:
\f0\b0  The inline upload flow, pre-populated for this event.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 The upload flow\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The upload experience is the most important UX moment on the platform. If it's too slow or requires too many steps, fans will post to Instagram instead and Showside gets nothing.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

